Q23¶

In [126]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

worldbank['log_gdpPercap'] = np.log(worldbank['gdpPercap'])

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(worldbank['log_gdpPercap'], worldbank['lifeExp'], alpha=0.7)
plt.title('Scatter Plot of Life Expectancy vs Log of GDP per Capita', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('Log of GDP per Capita', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy', fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)
plt.show()

Drawing from this plot and the one in question number 25, I can see that there is a positive correlation between GDP and life expectancy. They relationship seems to be that the higher the GDP, the higher the life expectancy. There also seems to be some outliar countries in the continent of Asia, but overall, the trend seems positive with most of the higher life expectancy being in the Americas and Europe.This can be explained by the fact that higher GDP countries tend to have better infastructure, water treatment, and medical assets. The higher qualifty of life from these more developed nations would explain the relationship seen on the charts.¶

Q24¶

In [128]:
import seaborn as sns

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.scatterplot(
    data=worldbank,
    x='log_gdpPercap',
    y='lifeExp',
    hue='continent',
    palette='tab10',
    alpha=0.7
)
plt.title('Scatter Plot of Life Expectancy vs Log of GDP per Capita (Colored by Continent)', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('Log of GDP per Capita', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy', fontsize=12)
plt.legend(title='Continent', fontsize=10)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)
plt.show()

In [140]:
import altair as alt

scatter_plot = alt.Chart(worldbank).mark_circle(size=60, opacity=0.7).encode(
    x=alt.X('log_gdpPercap', title='Log of GDP per Capita'),
    y=alt.Y('lifeExp', title='Life Expectancy'),
    color=alt.Color('continent', title='Continent'),
    tooltip=['continent', 'country', 'year']
).properties(
    title='Scatter Plot of Life Expectancy vs Log of GDP per Capita by Continent',
    width=800,
    height=500
)
